Title : Comet Mountain (British Columbia)
Text : '''Comet Mountain''', 1742 m (5715 feet),<ref>[http://bivouac.com/MtnPg.asp?MtnId=3236 Bivouac Mountain Encyclopedia entry]</ref> is a [[mountain]] in the [[Kitimat Ranges]] of [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]], located immediately west of the head of [[Dean Channel]] in the [[British Columbia Coast|Central Coast region]] of that province, to the northwest of the town of [[Bella Coola, British Columbia|Bella Coola]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/11543.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Comet Mountain"]</ref>  The former [[Nuxalk]] village and still-Indian reserve [[Kimsquit]] is located immediately east across Dean Channel, [[Chatscah Indian Reserve No. 2]] is immediately north at the mouth of the [[Kimsquit River]].

